net.minecraftforge.common

类 ModDimension

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.minecraftforge.registries.ForgeRegistryEntry<ModDimension>
      • net.minecraftforge.common.ModDimension
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    IForgeRegistryEntry<ModDimension>

    public abstract class ModDimension
extends ForgeRegistryEntry<ModDimension>
    In 1.13.2, Mojang made DimensionType as the unique holder/identifier for each Dimension. We used to be able to create custom Dimensions separate from DimensionType. But now that they are hard linked to a single instance, this is the new class that defines the 'template' for new dimensions.

      • write

        public void write(PacketBuffer buffer,
                  boolean network)
        Serialize any necessary data, this is called both when saving the world on the server. And when sent over the network to the client.
        参数:
        buffer - The data buffer to write to.
        network - true when sent over the network, so you can only data needed by the client.

      • read

        public void read(PacketBuffer buffer,
                 boolean network)
        Deserialize any necessary data, this is called both when saving the world on the server. And when sent over the network to the client.
        参数:
        buffer - The data buffer to write to.
        network - true when sent over the network, so you can only data needed by the client.

      • withFactory

        public static ModDimension withFactory(java.util.function.BiFunction<World,DimensionType,? extends Dimension> factory)
        Convenience method for generating a ModDimension with a specific factory but no extra data handling behaviour. Extend ModDimension to override other methods.
        参数:
        factory - Factory for creating Dimension instances from DimType and World.
        返回:
        A custom ModDimension with that factory.
